div.p:
To this end, the Netherlands Government shall invite, immediately after
                            the convention shall have been signed by the plenipotentiaries of the
                            powers who have taken part in the conference, all the powers of Europe
                            and of America not represented at the conference, to wit, the Argentine
                            Republic; Austro-Hungary; Belgium; Bolivia; Brazil; Bulgaria; Chile;
                            Colombia; Costa Rica; Republic of Cuba; Denmark; Dominican Republic;
                            Republic of Ecuador; Spain; Greece; Guatemala; Republic of Haiti;
                            Honduras; Luxemburg; Mexico; Montenegro; Nicaragua; Norway; Panama;
                            Paraguay; Peru; Roumania; Salvador; Servia; Sweden; Switzerland; Turkey;
                            Uruguay; United States of Venezuela, to designate a delegate armed with
                            the full powers necessary for the signing of the convention at The
                            Hague.
